                <h2 class="heading-sec u-margin-bottom-small">The River of Cruelty</h2>
                <p class="popup__text">
                    The "River of Cruelty" is a metaphor describing how cruel behaviors move freely from person to person and are passed down through generations. It is well described as a river, as it flows from parent to child, impacting each generation. We did not have a choice when we landed in the River. We were "thrown in" before we were old enough, or big enough, to prevent it.
                    Once in the River, we are often resourceful and develop skills that help us to survive. These skills might incude becoming self-centered/self-less, or isolating/seeking attention. Other strategies include repressing emotions or becoming rebellious or angry. While these and many other skills are obviously problematic, they also serve the purpose of helping people survive the River. Problems often show up later as we discover that the very skills that helped us survive, now serve to sabotage our quest for healthy relationships, and a more meaningful existence. These survival tools, while invaluable in helping us exist in the River of Cruelty, actually create a path for the River to continue to flow through future generations.Understanding how we entered the River in the first place is crucial to understanding the process of getting out.
                </p>
